) in a subdirectory instead of the root directory.'=>'The WordPress URL and the Site URL can be the same (example.com) or different; for example, having the WordPress core files (example.com/wordpress) in a subdirectory instead of the root directory.','Most themes display the site title at the top of every page, in the title bar of the browser, and as the identifying name for syndicated feeds. The tagline is also displayed by many themes.'=>'Most themes display the site title at the top of every page, in the title bar of the browser, and as the identifying name for syndicated feeds. The tagline is also displayed by many themes.','The fields on this screen determine some of the basics of your site setup.'=>'The fields on this screen determine some of the basics of your site setup.','timezone date formatY-m-d H:i:s'=>'Y-m-d H:i:s','General Settings'=>'General Settings','Create New Page'=>'Create New Page','There are no pages.'=>'There are no pages.','Or:'=>'Or:','Use This Page'=>'Use This Page','Select a Privacy Policy page'=>'Select a Privacy Policy page','Change your Privacy Policy page'=>'Change your Privacy Policy page','Need help putting together your new Privacy Policy page? <a href="%1$s" %2$s>Check out our guide%3$s</a> for recommendations on what content to include, along with policies suggested by your plugins and theme.'=>'Need help putting together your new Privacy Policy page? <a href="%1$s" %2$s>Check out our guide%3$s</a> for recommendations on what content to include, along with policies suggested by your plugins and theme.','<a href="%1$s">Edit</a> or <a href="%2$s">preview</a> your Privacy Policy page content.'=>'<a href="%1$s">Edit</a> or <a href="%2$s">preview</a> your Privacy Policy page content.','<a href="%1$s">Edit</a> or <a href="%2$s">view</a> your Privacy Policy page content.'=>'<a href="%1$s">Edit</a> or <a href="%2$s">view</a> your Privacy Policy page content.','We would also suggest reviewing your Privacy Policy from time to time, especi